---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SectionHeading from '@/components/SectionHeading.astro';
import SiteTreeHeader from '@/components/SiteTreeHeader.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="A short introduction to C M Nafi and the intent behind the site.">
  <SiteTreeHeader
    branch="connect"
    currentHref="/about"
    title="About"
    description="A short explanation of the site, the public system behind it, and the kind of work it is meant to hold."
  />

  <section class="page-section narrow-stack">
    <SectionHeading
      eyebrow="About"
      title="A digital home base for thoughtful work"
      description="This site is designed less like a portfolio and more like a public operating system — a place to gather writing, tools, experiments, and the ideas connecting them."
    />
    <div class="panel prose">
      <p>
        I’m interested in what happens when strong product taste meets deep curiosity: data tools that feel humane,
        writing that sharpens thinking, and systems that make public work easier to sustain.
      </p>
      <p>
        Some things here are finished, some are early, and some are intentionally unfinished. That is part of the point.
        The site is built to hold work in motion.
      </p>
      <p>
        Over time, this space will grow to include essays, project overviews, modular apps, notes, and live snapshots of
        what is currently brewing.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
